text:
Concord Street, south side, west from Pearl Street. A view of Public School No. 1. Old entrance was on Concord Street. At right, is a view of the Elevated structure of the B.M.T Lines. The Adams Street side, built in 1842, was still used in 1929.

1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Pearl Street, south from (No. 272) but not including Concord Street, showing the Long Island University, at the S.W. corner of Tillary Street.

June 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
